description:
Raining Down

Kalizarian troops secretly gather in the city as the Trolls travel the final leg of their desperate trip. The Earl and his chamberlain however, are distracted with more pressing problems - how to get rid of the prince without gaining the attention of the Ravenwood cousins. Meanwhile, Ravenwood begins to question the whole purpose of the quest and even his own destiny, but little does everyone know that all their problems are just beginning!
name: Raining Down

description: Toby continues the investigation into the murder committed in the Silver Bay. The discovery of subsequent secrets from the victim's past raises multiple questions and leads to some unexpected conclusions.

Bayani, a boy of 11, is desperately trying to care for his sick father (a fisherman) and keep food on the table for his small family. Unfortunately, the sun has been shining down on the islands for the last month and night refuses to fall. The land is growing parched from the constant heat and the fish are moving further and further away from shore. During this disaster, the rain god, Pati', recruits Bayani to undertake a quest rescuing the nine kidnapped daughters of Lady Moon from the horrible monsters of lore. Bayani embarks on a great adventure with his friend, Tala, and using their wits, the kids defeat one hideous creature after another in their quest to rescue each of the Moon's daughters and ultimately save their village. Collects Bayani's first three amazing adventures for readers of all ages to enjoy.
name: Volume 1: An Adventure Begins!

volume.name: Bayani and the Nine Daughters of the Moon

description: Leading Geisha and unofficial Yakuza assassin, Kimi, is missing, in the wake of her lover's murder, leaving Corrupt Government official Osamu primed to infiltrate the Government with his Yakuza army and worryingly for Kimi's sisters: control Gion. Meanwhile in a small village, a girl is found floating in the river.

Elvis vs Aliens: Devil in Disguise

In a classic case of mistaken identity, an invading alien force mistakes the King of Rock and Roll for the King of the planet Earth. For their troubles these aliens get a smash hit butt whipping courtesy of the kung fu fighting King. Problem solved, right? Far from it. These sneaky aliens have a trick up their space sleeve and unleash the ultimate terror.
name: Elvis vs Aliens: Devil in Disguise

description:
A fairy tale written for modern, blended families, writer Kristen Grace and illustrator Natasha Alterici combine their gifts to tell a magical story about an very unusual royal family.

Unsatisfied with fairytales which routinely vilify stepmothers, author Kristen Grace wanted to write a story that reflected the truth about the families she knew that were centered around strong and loving stepmothers. "My own daughter has a wonderful stepmother. When I couldn't find a story with a good stepmother in it for her last Mother's Day, I decided I would have to write my own."

volume.name: Feminist Fairy Tales: The Stepmother Who Dreamed Of Feathers

description:
When the FBI closes Desmodus, Lukos, Francesca, Rags and Gilda's monsters-only school, they are forced by their parents to attend a public school to continue their education. Now, they must try to fool their classmates and faculty all while navigating the horrors of growing up!

Issue #1 includes the stories:

MONSTER ELEMENTARY

Written by Nicholas Doan * Art by Caanan Grall

WHY AM I DlFFERENT? PART ONE

Written by Nicholas Doan * Art by Caanan Grall

ADDlCTED TO JUlCE PART ONE

Written by Nicholas Doan * Art by Christopher Tupa

He is a man without a name...without a memory. He is a man without a past…and apparently without a future. As he attempts to discover the secret of his past and his name, he finds himself drawn into an ancient battleground which has its basis in the bloodthirsty rites of the supposedly extinct Aztec Empire. The violent sacrifical rituals of a sun worshipping tribe somehow hold a key to his past but he must delve deeper into those horrible ceremonies for the secrets, knowing that if he survives, he will have to live with the answers. Now on the streets of modern day Mexico City our Nameless man finds findself attempting to protect the thousands of forgotten street children that inhabit the sprawling metropolis. They are being abducted and used as human sacrifices to an ancient Aztec God who wishes to take physical form and begin a reign of terror on Earth. And Nameless is the only one that stands in its way. Collects issues 1-5. From the mind of Joe Pruett (X-Men Unlimited, Wolverine, Cable) and Phil Hester (Swamp Thing, Green Arrow) and artist Bruce McCorkindale (Green Hornet, Godzilla).
name: GN

Prince, a prolific musician from Minneapolis, started a musical revolution with the hits "1999," "Little Red Corvette," "When Doves Cry," "Purple Rain," "Batdance," and more, challenging even the "King of Pop," Michael Jackson, for chart supremacy during the 1980's. "Tribute: Prince Rogers Nelson" features a special cover by rock artist David Frizell.

Douglas Noble's short comics talk about the secrets held in seaside hotel rooms, of bodies waiting to be buried, and of waiting ghosts written in old stone. What We Know About Falling Apart is a restlessly inventive collection of unfriendly romance, twenty-first century torment, and grim hilarity.

volume.name: What We Know About Falling Apart

description:
They say that Hell is on Earth but for Alice, it’s a kind of Paradise….

Alice Matheson, the sexy and brilliant nurse of St. Mary’s Hospital in London, could be a surgeon - she has the capacities, nerves of steel and a high IQ - but she would run the risk of exposure. Because Alice is an angel of death,

a cold, calculating psychopath who kills her victims chosen amongst the hospital patients in terminal phase.

But things become complicated when one of her victims gets up despite the lethal dose she has just given him.

London then experiences the first hours of a new sort of epidemic: the dead are alive. And even for a serial killer, this is rather disturbing.

The hospital is ready for action and gets organized to treat the patients and to find a solution for the epidemic.
name: Jour Z

description:
A serial killer under pressure! The noose is tightening around Alice, the brilliant, psychopathic nurse plunged into the heart of a zombie epidemic…

Between Dr. Barry, who is becoming more and more audacious, Nurse Alexandra Paynes who caught her killing a patient, and the strange guy called Harold Butler who said he met her before, Alice is going through a bad phase which almost makes her forget the zombies. Still, it appears that the cause of the epidemic could come from the hospital itself…
name: Le Tueur en moi

description:
She is rich and overqualified, so why is she a nurse?

There is no doubt anymore: the epidemic comes from St. Mary’s Hospital. Eliott Kitson leads the enquiry and Jordan Barry becomes Suspect N° 1. In the meantime, our sociopathic nurse, Alice Matheson, is using her holidays to study zombies when she is called by an old “friend”: Amy.

Amy once taught her to pretend empathy and to display a spark of humanity on her cold face. Amy was beaten and asks her to save her. It is a chance for Alice to further her research. The timing is tight, hope less than small, and what Alice will find won’t be much to her liking.
name: Sauvez Amy !

description: Cerise is a little 11-year-old girl who is living alone with her mother. She dreams of becoming a novelist. Her favorite subject: people, and more specifically: adults. She likes to observe them and try to find out their secrets. Like for example Michel... Every Sunday, this old man goes into the woods carrying big buckets of paint. What does he do all day ? And why does he look so sad when he comes back at night ? Follow Cerise into the heart of the woods, for her first investigation.
name: Le Zoo pétrifié

description:
A new enigma for Cerise, and she will do anything to solve it!

Cerise is a little 11-year-old girl who is living alone with her mother. She dreams of becoming a novelist. Her favorite subject: people, and more specifically: adults. She likes to observe them and try to find out their secrets.

Take Elisabeth... every week, for the past twenty years this old lady borrows the same book from the library. Why? What about it is so important to her? What secret is it hiding that she has not discovered yet?
name: Le Livre d'Hector

description:
Between a comic strip and a personal diary, Cerise's investigations are all captivating, funny and moving!

Cerise is a little 11-year-old girl who is living alone with her mother. She dreams of becoming a novelist. Her favorite subject: people, and more specifically: adults. She likes to observe them and try to find out their secrets. This time, she is interested in Sandra... Her bookbinding studio is full of old books. But there is one that she has never repaired. Why? Did she even know that it was there? And what are the five treasures linked to the life of the young woman?

Cerise, Line and Erica will follow together this path full of clues, this double-barrelled investigation, to try to give back to Sandra what she lost so many years ago...
name: Le Dernier des Cinq Trésors

description:
Cerise’s Notebooks, a series of fresh and sweet enquiries midway between a comic book and a private diary !

Holiday time has come! A visit to a strange manor house leads to a new enquiry: each room is an enigma, each object a clue. But there are older secrets just begging to be revealed. Who is this

faceless goddess sitting in a secret room? Where is the missing piece to that picture?

But, above all, who is pulling the strings of this new mystery? If Cerise can’t solve the puzzle in time, the consequences may be terrible…
name: La Déesse sans visage

description:
The confrontation of two representatives of illustrious antique cultures: a Roman soldier and a Chinese Prince. A voyage to the ends of the world, halfway between a historical comic book and a powerful peplum.

In 53BC, the battle of Carrhae ends with the defeat of the Romans. Numa, a legionnaire, is a prisoner of the Parthians and deported towards the East, very far from Rome. He constantly tries to escape: to flee from his jailers and recover his freedom; and also to warn Caesar of the incredible opportunities for enrichment lying in the fabulous land of the Seres. Will the Gods be kind to him?
name: L'Âge de fer
Richard Monroe - Who killed the fantastic Mister Leeds ?
Frédérick Abstraight - A cat in the barrel

L'Aube de la Guerriére du Nord

description: I see the tarot cards in my dreams. I turn them over in hopes of finding all the answers - Who am I? Where do I come from? Why are these people after me? But when I turn over the last card, it is always blank. My name is Kaguya. I thought I was an ordinary high-school girl. That is, until a crazy warrior appeared in my bedroom one night and transported me to another planet where people call me princess. Now, the questions in my dream are more urgent than ever. Will I ever get home again...or is this my home?
name: Vol. 1

description: Help! In the blink of an eye, my life has changed forever: one moment I am home safe in my bedroom, and the next, I am abducted by a crazy sorcerer and whisked away to another planet. I have no idea where I am or what I'm doing here, but I sure miss my mom, dad, and brother, and I'm not sure I'll ever see them again. People tell me I'm a princess... that I have the power to crush any world I wish. Yet, who do I believe or trust when my own world has been altered beyond my control?
name: Vol. 2

description: My name is Kaguya. In an instant, I went from being a regular high school student to a savior princess. Now I have been driven into another universe, where fate binds me to its salvation. I find myself traveling with a beautiful woman named Bambi and a strange doll named Gold that protects me at any cost. Both of them are supremely skilled in what they do, yet I feel utterly useless! I was hoping to befriend Bambi and prove my worth during our travels, but I cannot seem to find a way to make my mark. Along the way, we meet the wise Waseda, who comes from my world. Can he help me fulfill my given destiny and find my way back home?
name: Vol. 3

description: Orphaned in a war she can't remember, Kaguya is happy with her adopted family. But chaos returns when a mysterious boy tells her of her past as a princess from another world. With her guardian, Gold, by her side, Kaguya sets out on a journey from world to world to claim her birthright. Courted by some, hunted by others, Kaguya's destiny is feared by all? for it is her fate to decide which worlds will rule, and which shall die.
name: Vol. 4

description: The future of the universe is in my hands. I didn't ask for this, but it is mine. I am just an orphan. Unwanted. But now everyone wants me to be theirs - theirs or dead. My life in Japan was ordinary until Seeu and Idou kidnapped me and brought me to their worlds. Now I live with the silent Seeu, alone in his deserted palace. Some still call me by my name, Kaguya. Others call me the Princess of the Choosing. They say, with my black hair and blue eyes, that I am beautiful. But really I'm just scared. I must be brave. But all of my friends are gone! Where is Bambi? Who is Kagami? Will I ever know? Or will I die here with the rest of the Universe?
name: Vol. 5

description: My name is Kaguya, and I am prophesied to choose which one of the nine dimensional worlds is saved while the rest are destroyed. But in reality, I don't want anyone to die, so i made a declaration to all nine worlds that i wanted to save them all, not just one. I worry that all the worlds will not see things as clearly as I do since they have fought each other for so long. I don't know if they can ever change. If they don't we'll all be destroyed.
name: Vol. 6

description: Now that Kura has captured me, I, Kaguya, have no idea what to do. I'm beginning to suspect that there is more to the events that have surrounded me than the Emperor wants to let on, and I'm beginning to feel that no matter what world I choose to save, the universe is doomed anyway. I only hope that my brother Kagami can send me some kind of a message or sign about what to do. And I hope that Bambi and Prince Seeu will be able to save me before it's too late and Kura does something that will destroy us all....forever.
name: Vol. 7

description:
In the year 4886 of the Space Era, mankind proudly calls every far-flung corner of the universe home. The united powers of the Space Federation maintain peace and order across these myriad twinkles in the night sky, and an elite, highly classified military division known as "Special Operations" handles the most extreme of disturbances. Isagi Kayworthy, a member whose carefree attitude belies his advanced psychic abilities, is assigned the new recruit, Asheid Brown, as his partner, but he soon learns that Ashe's icy, aloof personality is the least of their concerns. No matter how he may try to flee, Ashe's body and soul is hopelessly ensnared in the cruel grip of a mad scientist known as "The Doctor," and Isagi has made the fatal mistake of touching The Doctor's "property!" Thrilling battles, shocking revelations, and intoxicating love all await in the first volume of Futaba Aoi and Mitsuba Kurenai's famous sci-fi epic, "Platina!"

Chapter 1 - 5.
name: -One Arm To Protect You-

description: The final battle grows nigh. The mad scientist, his doll, and the god of a foreign land... each man's life hangs by a thread, woven together, yet fraying apart. As the microcosmic war between The Doctor and Isagi comes to a head, whose arms will Ashe return to? The man who gave him life, or the man who gave his life meaning? All will be revealed in the jaw-dropping conclusion to the fan favorite, sci-fi epic "Platina"!
name: -The Promised Place-

description:
Sherlock Holmes’ darkest investigation.

From 1891 to 1894, Sherlock Holmes pretended to be dead.

Only a few people knew that he had survived his fight with James Moriarty. After many hardships, Holmes ended the charade and resumed his activities as a detective-advisor to Scotland Yard.

But his brother Mycroft seeks his help. The village of Keelodge has been put into quarantine; all its inhabitants have gone mad, bloodthirsty and cannibalistic. He needs him in the field because this drama is probably the result of a criminal act.
name: L'Affaire Keelodge
